<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb7bc97e0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s578"><num value="578">§ 578.</num><heading> Authority of the arbitrator</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An arbitrator to whom a dispute is referred under this subchapter may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb7bc97e1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s578/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> regulate the course of and conduct arbitral hearings;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb7bc97e2-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s578/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> administer oaths and affirmations;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb7bc97e3-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s578/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> compel the attendance of witnesses and production of evidence at the hearing under the provisions of <ref href="/us/usc/t9/s7">section 7 of title 9</ref> only to the extent the agency involved is otherwise authorized by law to do so; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb7bc97e4-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s578/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> make awards.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb7bc97e5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/101/552/s4/b">Pub. L. 101–552, § 4(b)</ref>, <date date="1990-11-15">Nov. 15, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/2742">104 Stat. 2742</ref>, § 588; renumbered § 578, <ref href="/us/pl/102/354/s3/b/2">Pub. L. 102–354, § 3(b)(2)</ref>, <date date="1992-08-26">Aug. 26, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/944">106 Stat. 944</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
